          <h2 class="gjs-heading" id="i6fase">Introduction to  <font color="#1ebc1c" id="izdpgk">Credit</font>
          </h2>
          <div id="iu92pn">Credit is an integral aspect of the modern financial landscape, influencing various aspects
            of our lives. Understanding what credit entails and its importance is crucial for making informed financial
            decisions.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="i667sv">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="iwlvnm">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="iplbsq">What is Credit?</h1>
          <div id="im6ssf">Credit is essentially the ability to borrow money or access goods or services with the
            understanding that payment will be made at a later date. It is a financial arrangement that plays a pivotal
            role in personal and business transactions. Whether it's obtaining a mortgage to buy a house, using a credit
            card for everyday purchases, or securing a business loan, credit facilitates economic activities.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="irxbe4">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="i2rtee">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="ixbtj5">Importance of Credit</h1>
          <div id="icx3y9">The significance of credit extends beyond mere convenience. It affects one's ability to make
            significant purchases, secure loans, and even influences job opportunities in some cases. A good credit
            history can open doors to favorable financial opportunities. Lenders and financial institutions use credit
            reports and scores to assess an individual's creditworthiness, determining the risk associated with lending
            money. This, in turn, affects the terms and interest rates offered, making credit management a critical
            aspect of personal finance.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="gjs-section" id="ib8m8n">
    <div class="gjs-container" id="icbh6u">
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="i7x5ai">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="i1xnm5">
          <h2 class="gjs-heading" id="ipm4mh">Types of  <font color="#1ebc1c" id="idga3f">Credit</font>
          </h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="ilsp1u">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="ims6rq">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="ii5mpk">Revolving Credit</h1>
          <div id="i64ro7">Revolving credit, like credit cards, allows individuals to borrow up to a certain limit and
            repay based on the amount used. Unlike installment credit, which involves fixed payments over a set period,
            revolving credit provides flexibility in repayments. However, managing revolving credit requires discipline
            to avoid accumulating excessive debt and negatively impacting credit scores.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="ijxqso">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="i47vuj">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="ivtvgk">Installment Credit</h1>
          <div id="i8473h">Installment credit involves borrowing a fixed amount and repaying it in regular installments
            over a specified period. This type of credit is common for major purchases like cars or appliances. Each
            payment contributes to both the principal and interest, allowing borrowers to budget more effectively.
            Installment credit can positively impact credit scores when payments are made consistently and on time.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="i50m3k">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="icgino">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="i6g3ic">Open Credit</h1>
          <div id="i4qfvw">Open credit, often used in business transactions, provides a preset credit limit with
            flexible repayment terms. It allows businesses to make purchases up to the approved limit without a fixed
            repayment schedule. While providing financial flexibility, open credit requires responsible management to
            avoid overextension and potential negative impacts on credit.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="ic7fcl">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="iyor18">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="i0ij58">Closed Credit</h1>
          <div id="ihp6a7">Closed credit, commonly associated with mortgages, involves borrowing for a specific purpose
            with a fixed repayment plan. Homebuyers agree to a set term and interest rate, making regular payments until
            the loan is fully repaid. Closed credit is structured, providing predictability in payments, but requires
            thorough financial planning to ensure long-term affordability.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="gjs-section" id="inm3c4">
