        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="ixaqmx">
          <h2 class="gjs-heading" id="ikpr54">Credit  <font color="#1ebc1c">Scores</font>
          </h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="ipqb29">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="ireb0i">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="iw2qgi">Understanding Credit Scores</h1>
          <div id="i6wgsm">Credit scores are numerical representations of an individual's creditworthiness, typically
            ranging from 300 to 850. FICO scores, the most widely used credit scores, consider various factors such as
            payment history, credit utilization, length of credit history, types of credit used, and new credit. The
            higher the score, the lower the perceived risk for lenders.<br /></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="iy6gmt">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="i9gyvi">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="iit3hj">Factors Affecting Credit Scores</h1>
          <div id="i6ej75">Multiple factors contribute to credit scores. Payment history, accounting for a significant
            portion, reflects how consistently payments are made. Credit utilization, the ratio of credit used to credit
            available, influences scores. The length of credit history considers how long accounts have been active,
            while the types of credit used and new credit inquiries contribute to the overall picture.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="gjs-grid-row" id="ifqb82">
        <div class="gjs-grid-column" id="i8w29e">
          <h1 class="gjs-heading" id="i9jjwi">Importance of a Good Credit Score</h1>
          <div id="iczvk2">Maintaining a good credit score is essential for accessing favorable financial products and
            terms. A high credit score increases the likelihood of approval for loans, credit cards, and mortgages. It
            also results in lower interest rates, saving individuals money over time. Additionally, a good credit score
            can impact non-financial aspects, such as job opportunities and rental applications, emphasizing the broader
            importance of credit management.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
